description: TEHRAN – Iranian Foreign Minister Abbas Araghchi said on Monday that Israel should not gloat over its airstrikes on Hezbollah and instead be worried about what is awaiting it.

description: TEHRAN – The chief commander of the Iranian Army, Major General Abdolrahim Mousavi, has issued a warning to Israel, telling them to "be ready" for a response to the recent assassination of Hezbollah Secretary General Sayyed Hassan Nasrallah.
title: Wait for Iran and the Resistance front's response, Army chief tells Israel

description: TEHRAN – Iranians gathered in the main squares of their cities across Iran, to slam Israel’s ongoing aggression in the region and express support for Resistance groups.

description: TEHRAN – The new wave of Israeli terrorism in the region, with Lebanon as the epicenter, has once again put the entire West Asia on edge.

description: The Zionist entity has been established on genocide, displacement and cowardly assassination of the Lebanese and Palestinian resistance leaders and members. The latest of which was the assassination of the leader of the Lebanese resistance, His Eminence Shaheed Sayyed Hassan Nasrallah (R).

description: TEHRAN – Iranian President Masoud Pezeshkian declared that the world should recognize that the blood of Sayyed Hassan Nasrallah and his associates will fuel a strong resistance against tyranny and oppression.

description: TEHRAN – In a recent press briefing, Nasser Kanaani, the spokesman for Iran’s Foreign Ministry, asserted that Israel will face consequences for its actions, emphasizing that none of its "crimes" will go unanswered.

description: TEHRAN – The Iranian Vice President has stated that Islamic nations must act promptly and decisively to assist Lebanon and Palestine, given the international community's inaction and lack of resolve in addressing their crises.

description: TEHRAN – The Police Command Information Center of Sistan and Baluchistan province has reported the assassination of three Iranian military personnel by armed bandits in the region.

description: TEHRAN – Iranian lawmakers have stated that the martyrdom of Hezbollah Leader Seyyed Hassan Nasrallah bolsters the anti-Zionist movement and contributes to the decline of this illegitimate regime.

description: TEHRAN – A high-ranking IRGC commander and military advisor to the Leader of the Islamic Revolution, in a letter to the family of Brigadier General Abbas Nilforushan, highlighted that the sacrifices of martyrs made by Resistance commanders serve as the motivating force in the continuous fight for the liberation of Al-Quds.

description: TEHRAN - Al Sadd SC secured their first win in the AFC Champions League Elite 2024-25 on Monday as an own goal from Hossein Hosseini and a second half penalty from Akram Afif earned Felix Sanchez’s side a 2-0 victory over Esteghlal at Jassim bin Hamad Stadium in Doha.
title: Esteghlal lose to Al Sadd in AFC Champions League Elite 2024-25

description: TEHRAN - Pakhtakor football team came from behind to force a 1-1 draw with Persepolis in their AFC Champions League Elite 2024/25 tie on Monday.
title: Persepolis held by Pakhtakor in AFC Champions League Elite 2024/25

description: TEHRAN -Mikhail Mishustin, the Prime Minister of Russia, has emphasized the importance of strengthening relations between Moscow and Tehran, particularly highlighting the efforts to enhance trade and economic cooperation in key sectors such as transportation, energy, industry, and agriculture.

description: TEHRAN- Sheikh Naim Qassem, the Hezbollah deputy secretary-general, addressed several points in a televised address following the martyrdom of Sayyed Hassan Nasrallah.

description: TEHRAN- Israel appears to be preparing to carry out its long-standing threat of initiating a ground invasion of Lebanon despite a growing international outcry against the regime’s warmongering in the region.

description: Gaza’s “healthcare sector is still gradually deteriorating” nearly a year on since the war started, according to Dr Mohammed Abu Mughaisib, the deputy medical coordinator for Doctors Without Borders in Gaza.

description: At least 100,000 people have crossed from Lebanon into Syria fleeing Israel’s bombardment, the UN refugee agency’s chief said.
title: Israeli raids force 100,000 to flee Lebanon for Syria

description: British NGO Mines Advisory Group (MAG), which operates in Lebanon, has launched a campaign to advise people of the dangers of unexploded ordnance.
title: Campaign launched to raise awareness on unexploded ordnance in Lebanon

description: SHANGHAI, China - The curtain descended on the United Nations Summit of the Future on September 23 in New York. It ushered in many new opportunities and new ideas for global governance. Although the world is still facing a series of global challenges such as war, poverty and displacement, there is a general consensus among participants that working together to reduce the security deficit, promote sustainable human development, oppose zero-sum games, and enhance the discourse power of the Global South can cope with chaos and risks.
title: A better future for humanity cannot be achieved without upholding globalization and multipolarity

description: TEHRAN- English director Danny Boyle’s 2013 movie “Trance” was reviewed during a session at the Arasbaran Cultural Center in Tehran on Sunday.

description: TEHRAN-Iranian animators received two awards at the 27th edition of the Religion Today Film Festival in Trento, Italy.

description: TEHRAN- Iranian short documentary “Standing with the Wolf”, co-directed by Saeed Nabi and Maryam Khadivi, received an award from the Irkutsk Regional Museum of Local Lore named after Muravyov-Amursky at the 23rd edition of the Baikal International Film Festival of Documentary and Popular-Science Films “People and Environment”, which concluded in Irkutsk, Russia on Saturday.
title: “Standing with the Wolf” receives award at Russian festival

description: TEHRAN – The eighth edition of a marathon running is scheduled to be held in the touristic Shahdad region of the UNESCO-registered Lut Desert on October 17.

description: A woman is picking pistachios on a farm in the northeastern North Khorasan Province, September 30, 2024. Pistachio is cultivated across 5,900 hectares of land in the province.

description: TEHRAN – Iran defeated Pakistan 41-34 to win the title of the 2024 World Beach Kabaddi Championship Sunday night.
